            <article class="header-container" data-uuid="51f21fbe3e844ff39222a7a57c2ae003">
                <div class="header-element" data-uuid="a0f8dd39022e4ea29f65780b3b5d4649">
                    <h1 data-uuid="8bb67625b9f04a2fada4f723d841eac7">Growth of the Cotton Industry </h1>
                    <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="a099e003f2da4279a6235b79b2d48a02"></div>
                    <h2 data-uuid="6bcc7f9060034904ba197e2d1fa15f42">The Big Idea</h2>
                    <p data-uuid="d76a78a6d0424ca3bf0f310a1d6b7779">The invention of the cotton
                        gin made the South a one-crop economy and increased the need for slave labor.</p>
                </div>
            </article>
            <article data-uuid="dc6849c823184c9eab484fd3f1e3f5ec">
                <h3 class="if-you-were-there" data-uuid="29e128574c2b4750ace16102a92a60ad">If YOU were there...</h3>
                <p data-uuid="9cb1247313564c0d81374bfe41fee306">You are a field-worker on a
                    cotton farm in the South in about 1800. Your job is to separate the seeds from
                    the cotton fibers. It is dull, tiring work because the tiny seeds are tangled
                    in the fibers. Sometimes it takes you a whole day just to clean one pound of cotton!
                    Now you hear that someone has invented a machine that can clean cotton 50 times
                    faster than by hand.</p>
            </article>
